To analyze the sentence, we first need to identify the tokens (words and punctuation) and their grammatical dependencies. 

1. När (adv-modifier -> befolkningen) - distance: 1
2. befolkningen (subject -> ökar) - distance: 1
3. ökar (verb-root) - distance: 0
4. så (adv-modifier -> snabbt) - distance: 1
5. snabbt (adv-modifier -> ökar) - distance: 2
6. blir (verb-root) - distance: 0
7. det (subject -> blir) - distance: 1
8. svårt (object -> blir) - distance: 2
9. att (infinitive-marker -> odla) - distance: 3
10. odla (infinitive-verb -> att) - distance: 0 (non-root, considering the dependency to och and assuming it to be the root)
11. tillräckligt (adj-modifier -> mycket) - distance: 1
12. mycket (adj-modifier -> mat) - distance: 2
13. mat (object -> odla) - distance: 3
14. och (conjunction -> svårt, and the second clause) - distance: N/A, since it is a coordinator
15. därför (adv-modifier -> flyttar) - distance: 1
16. flyttar (verb-root) - distance: 0
17. man (subject -> flyttar) - distance: 3
18. in (adv-modifier -> till) - distance: 1
19. till (preposition -> städerna) - distance: 0 (non-root, considering the dependency to in and städerna to be modifying/objects to each other under 'till')
20. städerna (object -> till) - distance: 3
21. för (preposition -> att) - distance: 0 (non-root, considering the dependency to att and assuming it to be the object)
22. att (infinitive-marker -> söka) - distance: 0 (non-root, considering the dependency to för)
23. söka (infinitive-verb -> att) - distance: 0 (non-root, considering the dependency to och and assuming it to be the root)
24. mat (object -> söka) - distance: 2
25. och (conjunction -> arbete) - distance: N/A
26. arbete (object -> söka) - distance: 4
27. . (punctuation) - distance: 26, depends on the end of the sentence.

Dependency distances calculated above have some variables, but one must define all the non-root, coordinators or punctuations (söka, in, till, för, .) with final roots or prior. Assuming, a revised simplified with non-root coordinating words and prepositions linked distance to the nearest prior clause object or root. The distance determined can then be taken and applied:

